Heat your #oven{} to 220 degrees, then peel and finely dice half the @onion{1/2} and the @garlic clove{1}. Clean the @button mushrooms{1}(cleaned with a damp cloth) and then slice them thinly. Cut the @potato{1.5} in half lengthways and then again lengthways into finger sized wedges.

> Mushrooms are like sponges so don't wash them in lots of water.

Toss the potato wedges in @oil{1%tbsp}, @salt{1/2%tsp} and lay on a #baking tray{}. Cook on the top shelf of the #oven{} for ~{15-20%mins} until golden.

Mix the @minced beef{250%g} with @salt{1/4%tsp} and a good few grinds of @black pepper{}. Divide the mixture into 2 and form patties.

> Press the meat together only as hard as you need to for it to stick. The more loosely packed the meat the better the burger!

Split your @brioche bun{2}(halved) and toast them lightly in a dry pan or under the #grill{}.

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a pan, add the onions and cook over a medium heat for ~{3%mins}. Add the mushrooms and continue to cook for ~{5%mins} or until soft. Add the garlic for the final minute of cooking along with @salt{1/4%tsp} and some @pepper{}. Remove from the #pan{} and keep warm.

Heat a further @olive oil{1/2%tbsp} on medium-high heat in the pan. Once hot, gently add your burgers and cook for around ~{3-4%mins} on each side. Top each with a slice of @cheese{2%slices} for the final minute of cooking. Add @water{1%tbsp} to the pan and cover with a #lid{} to create steam to melt the cheese.

Pile the mushroom mixture onto the bun, top with the burger and then the @Steve's leaves{1}. Serve with the potato wedges and enjoy!